The course gives an overview about historical and theoretical background of the psychological counselling, gives an introduction to the structure of the counseling covering themes like counseling process, structure of session, main counselling skills, traits of the counsellor, ethical dilemmas, problems.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aim is to introduce counselling psychology and to give theoretical knowledge about different skills and subjects what are needed  in counselling process.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Understands counselling psychology as a research field and an applied field. Can describe the counselling process and session. Has an overview about main counselling skills. Knows professional ethics and can recognize ethical dilemmas. Understands the purpose of psychological assessment in the counselling process and is aware of restrictions in using it in counselling. Is aware of the need of professional development and the main ways in supporting it (i.e. supervision).
